summary: Hello! Sorry if I’m bothering you with something simple, but I’m just a bit worried is all. I started my journey around Hoenn a...
question: Hello! Sorry if I’m bothering you with something simple, but I’m just a bit worried is all. I started my journey around Hoenn a few weeks back, one of the first Pokémon that I had join my team was that of a Zigzagoon. He really has become one of my best friends. Recently he’s been acting rather strange. Once a lively and energetic little guy, he’s seemingly a lot slower all of a sudden, not as peppy as he used to be either. Actually, he seems a lot more aggressive. Lashing out a lot. Any advice?
answer:
The only thing I can think of is to try and get a hold of it and check it closely. You’re looking for either some injuries, some signs external signs of illness, some off pattern pieces for it, or some out of place black fur deep into parts of it’s fur.

If it’s something with the latter two, then you need to call it out and then search quite a bit as if the pattern’s off in areas or there’s black fur, it’s going to actually be a Zorua or Zoroark in disguise that’s upset you insist on it staying with you. They’re incredibly rare in Hoenn, but not unheard of.

If it’s the former two, however, it means your Zigzagoon is either badly injured or sick, and is lashing out in a defensive state. Zigzagoon aren’t nearly as well equipped for protection as the other common Hoenn pokemon, so it’s common that if they haven’t been able to recover properly they’ll get aggressive to discourage predators and other threats. You’ll need to take it to a Pokemon Center immediately.

summary: what i really appreciate about detective pikachu is that they had 809 pokemon to choose from, and they so easily could’ve stuck...
body: what i really appreciate about detective pikachu is that they had 809 pokemon to choose from, and they so easily could’ve stuck with some of the more normal looking dudes, but instead they really Went For It. the first time we’re seeing dynamic, realistic versions of pokemon and they’re featuring shit like ludicolo? loudred? mR. MIME? sticking the most bizarre affront to god lookin motherfuckers right there in the trailer, offering them up as the first example of what this movie has to offer like they aren’t the stuff of nightmares? gotta admire that bravery
